Janua.Test.Server.Intf Namespace

Summary

This is a Sample Demo and Documentation on how to build a full Orm-Server solution with Janua Orm and Server Framework.

Note

The basic Interface for a schema is made this way:

  • A Generic Storage Definition
  • A More specific Storage Dataset defiition
  • A Cache System.
  • A Server Definition
  • A Factory to help to obtain all classes implementing those interfaces

Interfaces
 NameDescription
IJanuaDBTestStorage

Extends The basic interface with Local/Remote DB Dataset objects.

IJanuaServerTest

Interface for specific 'Test' Server. It contains all objects, properties and methods to define the 'contract' for a model implementation of Test structure

IJanuaServerTestCache

Caching Objects, such as Server(s) or Storage(s) using a thread pool access can be useful for scaling

IJanuaServerTestFactory

Factory Interface (can be globally defined) to create Server and Storage(s) according to the underlying data storage management library (DB, Web Service and so on).

IJanuaTestStorage

Template for Test Storage Recorset Sources. Used for local/remote test storage

Top
Remarks

Always include januacore.inc. And use Janua.Orm.* and Janua.Server.intf units. Orm Impl Template is requested to help create and setup server factory
